106
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:18,730
You didn't see his face.

107
00:04:18,730 --> 00:04:20,250
When I think of it now,

108
00:04:20,370 --> 00:04:21,490
I'm like…

109
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:24,470
He's such an annoyance.

110
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:28,540
I'll go do the cleaning.

111
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:31,770
Look at them.

112
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:33,730
They all understand the importance of this,

113
00:04:34,020 --> 00:04:34,450
don't they?

114
00:04:34,450 --> 00:04:35,390
And you knew

115
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:36,590
that Lou Mingye would come today.

116
00:04:36,590 --> 00:04:38,030
Couldn't you just suck it up?

117
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:40,380
He's famous for being difficult.

118
00:04:40,790 --> 00:04:41,900
Everyone in the station knows that.

119
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:43,690
Did you have to pit yourself against him?

120
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:47,520
A loner can't get far.

121
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:49,010
Do you know what I mean?

122
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:51,010
To be honest,

123
00:04:51,030 --> 00:04:53,670
you're indeed at fault today.

124
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:55,100
You know what?

125
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,420
It's fine to make a mistake.

126
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:58,080
As long as you correct it,

127
00:04:58,260 --> 00:04:59,980
you're still a good firefighter.

128
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:01,430
To be honest…

129
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:03,090
To be honest, you should go back.

130
00:05:03,090 --> 00:05:04,050
Where do you want me to go?

131
00:05:04,090 --> 00:05:05,130
Stop right there!

132
00:05:06,930 --> 00:05:08,370
To be honest,

133
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:08,940
you should look at this.

134
