Only the three of you applaud this idea, right?

210
00:07:36,660 --> 00:07:38,260
How could you say that?

211
00:07:38,420 --> 00:07:39,780
Anyone with objections stands up.

212
00:07:41,020 --> 00:07:41,590
Look.

213
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:42,900
Everyone likes this idea.

214
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,020
Right?

215
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:44,900
Look, Instructor.

216
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:46,100
This is what we all want.

217
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:48,110
Every time we come back from a mission,

218
00:07:48,110 --> 00:07:49,340
there's no food left for us.

219
00:07:49,390 --> 00:07:51,220
We need to eat to stay strong.

220
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:52,540
My grandma told me

221
00:07:52,620 --> 00:07:53,790
that skipping meals is a bad habit.

222
00:07:53,990 --> 00:07:55,580
You said yourself

223
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:58,420
that to save others, we need to take good care of ourselves first.

224
00:07:58,630 --> 00:07:59,980
So I think

225
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:02,940
eating well is taking good care of ourselves

226
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:03,980
so that

227
00:08:03,980 --> 00:08:05,550
we can better protect the people

228
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:07,140
and their property, right?

229
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:08,860
Yes.

230
00:08:11,380 --> 00:08:12,140
I-I…

231
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:12,470
Bro.

232
00:08:12,820 --> 00:08:13,500
You have objections?

233
00:08:13,980 --> 00:08:16,220
I have to say it's a good idea.

234
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:16,940
That's right.

235
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:20,580
Well…

236
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:22,150
Instructor Yang, Director Lin.

237
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:23,420
